SENATE BILL 930
P6 6lr3495
By: Senator Harris
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Budget and Taxation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Police Retirement System – Special Disability Retirement
3 FOR the purpose of allowing certain retirees of the State Police Retirement System to apply
4 for a certain special disability retirement allowance; and generally relating to special
5 disability retirement benefits in the State Police Retirement System.
6 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
7 Article – State Personnel and Pensions
8 Section 24–401.1(a), (f), (g), and (k)
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – State Personnel and Pensions
14 24–401.1.
15 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
16 (2) “DROP” means the Deferred Retirement Option Program established
17 under this section.
18 (3) “DROP member” means a member of the State Police Retirement
19 System who:
20 (i) is eligible to participate in the DROP as provided in subsection
21 (c) of this section; and
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0930*

2 SENATE BILL 930
1 (ii) elects to participate in the DROP as provided in subsection (e) of
2 this section.
3 (f) (1) A DROP member’s participation in the DROP shall commence on the
4 first day of the month following acceptance by the Board of Trustees of the DROP member’s
5 completed election form, retirement application form, and any other information required
6 by the Board of Trustees.
7 (2) A DROP member is a retiree of the State Police Retirement System.
8 (g) Participation in the DROP ends if the DROP participant:
9 (1) separates from employment in accordance with the binding letter of
10 resignation submitted with the member’s election form;
11 (2) except for the Secretary of State Police, attains age 60;
12 (3) dies;
13 (4) is terminated from employment by the Maryland State Police at any
14 time before the date specified on the member’s election form;
15 (5) shortens the time period for participation in the DROP by delivering to
16 the Maryland State Police and the Board of Trustees written notice of the intent of the
17 DROP member to terminate employment; or
18 (6) accepts a special disability retirement allowance as provided in
19 subsection (k) of this section.
20 (k) (1) A DROP member is eligible to apply for a special disability retirement
21 allowance under § 29–111 of this article if after the DROP member commences
22 participation in the DROP:
23 (i) the member is totally and permanently incapacitated for duty
24 arising out of or in the course of the actual performance of duty that occurs while
25 participating in DROP, and without willful negligence of the member; and
26 (ii) the medical board certifies that:
27 1. the member is totally incapacitated, either mentally or
28 physically, for the further performance of duty by the occurrence described under item (i)
29 of this paragraph;
30 2. the incapacity is likely to be permanent; and
31 3. the member should be retired.

SENATE BILL 930 3
1 (2) (i) If a DROP member is granted a special disability retirement
2 allowance, the DROP member shall:
3 1. submit an application to the Board of Trustees, on the
4 form the Board of Trustees provides, to receive payment of the amount accrued in the DROP
5 in accordance with subsection (i) of this section;
6 2. execute a written waiver of any benefits to which the
7 DROP member may be entitled under the DROP; and
8 3. submit an application to retire with a special disability
9 retirement allowance, on the form the Board of Trustees provides, stating the effective date
10 of the DROP member’s retirement as a special disability retiree.
11 (ii) On acceptance of the application for payment and application to
12 retire, the Board of Trustees shall commence payment of a special disability allowance to
13 the DROP member as provided in § 29–111(c) of this article, except that the DROP
14 member’s average final compensation shall be computed as of the effective date of the
15 DROP member’s application for a special disability retirement allowance.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
17 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
18 (2) “Board” means the Board of Trustees for the State Retirement and
19 Pension System.
20 (3) “DROP” has the meaning stated under § 24–401.1 of the State
21 Personnel and Pensions Article.
22 (b) This section applies to an individual who:
23 (1) was a member of the State Police Retirement System;
24 (2) enrolled in DROP on or after July 1, 2020;
25 (3) prior to enrolling in DROP, was involved in a work–related accident;
26 and
27 (4) before July 1, 2026, ceased participation in DROP.
28 (c) (1) (i) An individual described under subsection (b) of this section may
29 submit an application for a special disability retirement allowance under § 29–111 of the
30 State Personnel and Pensions Article.
31 (ii) Notwithstanding § 24–401.1(k)(1)(i) of the State Personnel and
32 Pensions Article, the Board may award a special disability retirement allowance under §

4 SENATE BILL 930
1 29–111 of the State Personnel and Pensions Article for an individual described under
2 subsection (b) of this section.
3 (2) An individual described under subsection (b) of this section shall submit
4 an application for a special disability retirement allowance under § 29–111 of the State
5 Personnel and Pensions Article:
6 (i) on or before December 31, 2026; and
7 (ii) by submitting to the Board a form provided by the State
8 Retirement Agency for the purpose of applying for a special disability retirement allowance
9 under this Act.
10 (d) If the Board grants a special disability retirement allowance in accordance
11 with this section, the retiree shall be entitled to benefits:
12 (1) from the date of the award of a special disability retirement allowance,
13 in accordance with § 29–111 of the State Personnel and Pensions Article; and
14 (2) from the date on which benefits would have been paid in accordance
15 with the State Personnel and Pensions Article through the date of an award of a special
16 disability retirement allowance in accordance with this section, the difference between the
17 benefits that would have been paid under a special disability retirement allowance and the
18 benefits the retiree received prior to the award of a special disability retirement allowance.
19 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
20 1, 2026. It shall remain effective for a period of 6 months and, at the end of December 31,
21 2026, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be abrogated
22 and of no further force and effect.

